      <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 1rem; line-height: 1.5;">Quick answers to help you start renting, listing, and paying safely on RentIt.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-right">
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">How does peer-to-peer renting work?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          RentIt connects local item owners directly with renters.
          You simply search for the items you need near your location, select the rental dates, make a secure direct transfer to the owner, and coordinate handovers.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">Are payments safe and direct to owners?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          Yes! We support secure direct Pay-to-Seller methods including UPI QR Code and bank transfers.
          The transaction amount is routed directly to the owner's payout credentials without platform cuts.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">How does RentIt verify users' identities?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          To build community trust, all renters and sellers must submit their 12-digit Aadhaar number and copy of identity documents, which are audited and verified by administrators before renting is allowed.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-question">How is Gemini AI used in RentIt?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          RentIt utilizes Google Gemini AI to read item photos and draft automated descriptions, suggest appropriate local market rental rates, analyze reviews, and parse natural language search queries instantly.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- Auto-slider and FAQ scripts -->
<script>
  // Simple Carousel Slide Loop
  let currentSlide = 0;
  const track = document.getElementById('bannerTrack');
  const totalSlides = 3;

  function rotateCarousel() {
    currentSlide = (currentSlide + 1) % totalSlides;
    if(track) {
      track.style.transform = `translateX(-${currentSlide * 100}%)`;
    }
  }
  
  // Slide every 4 seconds
  setInterval(rotateCarousel, 4000);

  // FAQ toggle helper
  function toggleFaq(item) {
    // Toggle active class
    const isActive = item.classList.contains('active');
    
    // Close other items
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(el => {
      el.classList.remove('active');
      el.querySelector('.faq-toggle').textContent = '+';
    });

    if (!isActive) {
      item.classList.add('active');
      item.querySelector('.faq-toggle').textContent = '-';
    }
  }
</script>

